[medium] policies/secretsmanager_rotation_timeliness.rego:70 (correctness vs. the actual SDK/library)
ScheduleExpression-only rotation rules are valid in Secrets Manager and the collector represents missing AutomaticallyAfterDays as automatically_after_days=0. The current overdue rule requires automatically_after_days > 0, so a secret with schedule_expression="rate(30 days)" and a last rotation months ago produces no rotation_overdue finding at all. Pass 1 fixed the immediate false positive, but this now creates a false negative for stale scheduled rotations.
Suggested fix: Derive an effective cadence from rotation_rules.schedule_expression for supported rate(N day/days) expressions and use it in rotation_deadline_days when automatically_after_days is absent or zero; for unsupported cron/unknown expressions, emit an explicit skip_reason or require collector-normalized cadence evidence instead of silently passing.
Guidance: Fix policies/secretsmanager_rotation_timeliness.rego so ScheduleExpression-only rotations are evaluated when the schedule is a supported day-based rate. Keep automatically_after_days as the preferred cadence when it is > 0. Add schedule_expression := lower(trim_space(object.get(rotation_rules, "schedule_expression", ""))) and a local helper such as schedule_rate_days := days if regex.find_all_string_submatch_n("^rate\\(([0-9]+) days?\\)$", schedule_expression, 1) returns one match, then days := to_number(matches[0][1]) and days > 0. Add effective_rotation_days rules: one returning automatically_after_days when > 0, and one returning schedule_rate_days only when automatically_after_days is null or <= 0. Change rotation_deadline_days and rotation_overdue to use effective_rotation_days, not automatically_after_days directly. For unsupported non-empty schedules such as cron(...), do not silently pass stale rotations: add a skip_reason for resource_type secret + rotation_enabled + last_rotated_date != "" + no effective cadence, with guidance that the collector must provide a normalized cadence. Do not change rotation_never_executed; enabled rotation with empty last_rotated_date should still fail unless another finding's service-linked skip applies. Add tests in policies/secretsmanager_rotation_timeliness_test.rego: rate(30 days) with last rotation beyond 30 * data.rotation_grace_multiplier days triggers rotation_overdue; rate(1 day) singular parses; cron(...) with old last_rotated_date has no rotation_overdue and exposes skip_reason. Keep the existing recent rate(30 days) non-overdue test passing.
